1593<div>

1594<h2>

1595Your Guide to Patio Sets &amp; Outdoor Furniture</h2>

1596

1597

1598<p>

1599Outdoor furniture can transform your backyard, patio, or deck into a beautiful extension of your home. You can go simple and pair some lounge chairs with an outdoor fire pit, or you can go all out with a gazebo, a porch swing, and patio dining set. The choice is up to you!</p>

1600

1601

1602<p>

1603We want to be your resource in understanding everything you need to know about outdoor furniture, from outlining what the&nbsp;<a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-materials-outdoor-furniture/">

1604best materials for outdoor furniture</a>

1605 are to explaining&nbsp;<a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-clean-outdoor-cushions/">

1606how to clean outdoor cushions</a>

1607&nbsp;and other furniture items. With the help of our <a href="https://design.vevano.com/design-services/">

1608Vevano Home&rsquo;s expert designers</a>

1609, we share different types of outdoor furniture and how to style it and keep it clean.</p>

1610

1611

1612<h3>

1613Elevate Your Space with a New Patio Set</h3>

1614

1615

1616<p>

1617A patio set consists of dining and side tables, chairs, cushions, umbrellas, and more. Because there are so many styles and design options to choose from, you can personalize your patio set to fit your unique style and make it as comfortable as you&rsquo;d like.</p>

1618

1619

1620<p>

1621When selecting a patio set, take into consideration the size of the available space that you have. If the space is large, make sure the outdoor furniture that you choose fills the space and has enough seating for the typical amounts of guests that you will have over. On the other hand, if your space is smaller, make sure that it doesn&rsquo;t feel overcrowded with too much furniture or furniture that is too big.</p>

1622

1623

1624<p>

1625There are two types of patio sets: dining sets and lounge sets. Here&rsquo;s a brief overview of each.</p>

1626

1627

1628<h4>

1629<span style="font-size:18px;">

1630<strong>

1631Patio Dining Sets</strong>

1632</span>

1633</h4>

1634

1635

1636<p>

1637Dining sets are typically used for enjoying meals outside with family and friends. This piece of outdoor patio furniture should be comfortable enough for you and your guests to eat and converse for a couple of hours. That means that you&rsquo;ll want to look for furniture that is made of metal or wood and is furnished with plush pillows and cushions on the seat and the back. These patio dining sets consist of five to eleven different pieces including dining tables, chairs, cushions, umbrellas, etc.</p>

1638

1639

1640<h4>

1641<span style="font-size:18px;">

1642<strong>

1643Patio Lounge Sets</strong>

1644</span>

1645</h4>

1646

1647

1648<p>

1649Another popular option for patio sets is a lounge set. Imagine a warm summer night, conversing with family, and laughing together. Your patio lounge set would be the perfect location for this. Having a sofa and comfortable chairs made of weatherproof outdoor furniture material would be ideal so that your furniture does not rust with rain or fade with time. These patio lounge sets can consist of a coffee table or a couple of side tables, chairs, a hammock, a sofa or chaise lounge, and an umbrella to provide share while enjoying your backyard.</p>

1650

1651

1652<p>

1653If you&rsquo;re looking for something a little more simple and budget-friendly, you can take a look at bistro sets. These sets are composed of two chairs with a table in between. Bistro sets are a great option if you don&rsquo;t need a ton of seating, but still want to enjoy those summer nights outside.</p>

1654

1655

1656<h3>

1657Common Patio Set Materials</h3>

1658

1659

1660<p>

1661There are several different types of materials that patio sets are made of. We have compiled a list of the top four best outdoor weatherproof materials.</p>

1662

1663

1664<h4>

1665<span style="font-size:18px;">

1666<strong>

1667Wrought Iron</strong>

1668</span>

1669</h4>

1670

1671

1672<p>

1673Wrought iron makes for durable furniture and provides sturdy chairs and tables. Because of this, cast iron furniture is more heavy, so if you&rsquo;re wanting to move your furniture around a lot, remember that it may be more difficult to move. You will also want to make sure that your cast iron furniture has a weather resistant finish so that it does not rust when it gets wet.</p>

1674

1675

1676<h4>

1677<span style="font-size:18px;">

1678<strong>

1679Teak</strong>

1680</span>

1681</h4>

1682

1683

1684<p>

1685This material is a very popular option because teak is the hardest, strongest, and most durable of the hardwoods. Because of its ability to last long, many people choose teak for their outdoor furniture. Teak is also less maintenance than cast iron because it is already weather and pest resistant. The natural oils found in teak repel water, so you don&rsquo;t have to worry about it being exposed to the rain.</p>

1686

1687

1688<h4>

1689<span style="font-size:18px;">

1690<strong>

1691Sunbrella or Olefin</strong>

1692</span>

1693</h4>

1694

1695

1696<p>

1697Sunbrella and Olefin are highly-durable outdoor fabric materials. Both materials are fade- and water-resistant and hold up well under a variety of weather conditions&mdash;although we still recommend covering or stowing away outdoor furniture under extreme weather. Sunbrella tends to have better water-resistance, but Olefin is more durable and eco-friendly.</p>

1698

1699

1700<h4>

1701<span style="font-size:18px;">

1702<strong>

1703Concrete</strong>

1704</span>

1705</h4>

1706

1707

1708<p>

1709Concrete is a trending for outdoor furniture&mdash;and it&rsquo;s no surprise why. This highly durable, versatile material pairs well with most outdoor materials, including teak and wrought iron. Depending on how you style it, concrete can add a modern, sophisticated touch to your space or lend to a rustic ambience.</p>

1710

1711

1712<h4>

1713<span style="font-size:18px;">

1714<strong>

1715Synthetic Woven Resin</strong>

1716</span>

1717</h4>

1718

1719

1720<p>

1721Who doesn&rsquo;t love the look of rattan woven in a stylish criss-cross wicker pattern? Unfortunately, natural rattan and other plant fibers require lots of maintenance and are prone to fading and water damage. However, synthetic resin and plastic are wonderfully durable alternatives to natural plant fibers and can mimic the same classic wicker look and weaves you want in outdoor furniture. Look for synthetic woven textures made of high-density polyethylene (HDPE) for maximum durability.</p>

1722

1723

1724<h3>

1725How to Keep Your Outdoor Furniture Clean</h3>

1726

1727

1728<p>

1729To be able to enjoy your outdoor patio furniture for years to come, you will want to take care of it properly. Before purchasing any outdoor furniture, make sure that it is made of materials that are built to last and are rust resistant. You can then protect your furniture from harsh weather by using furniture covers. We recommend covering your outdoor furniture whenever you are not using it but especially when you are storing them away for the season.</p>

1730

1731

1732<p>

1733If you use pillows and cushions that have a protective case, you can throw the cases in the washer a couple of times a year so they look new again. If your cushions do not have a protective case or they are not machine washable, you can wash your furniture with the hose and dish soap to get some of those tough stains out of the fabric.</p>

1734

1735

1736<p>

1737When cleaning your cushions, use a hard brush to scrub out those hard stains, and then let them air dry in the sun. You&rsquo;ll want to make sure that you do this on a solid outdoor surface. For best results when cleaning your outdoor furniture cushions, use a pressure washer to get out tough stains.</p>

1738

1739

1740<p>

1741The effort that you will need to put in to maintain your set looking nice will depend on the climate where you live. Be sure to research and choose materials that respond well to your location&rsquo;s climate.</p>

1742

1743

1744<h3>

1745Outdoor Furniture Styling Tips</h3>

1746

1747

1748<p>

1749Because there are so many options of what you can do with outdoor furniture, the styling possibilities are endless! If desired, keep your patio set in a similar style as the rest of your house and rooms indoor. For example, if you have a modern kitchen, pair it with a modern outdoor furniture set. There are also contemporary, coastal, rustic, exotic, and so many more styles. Pick what you like the best and style it with some matching cushions and pillows and your patio set will &lsquo;wow&rsquo; your guests.</p>

1750

1751

1752<p>

1753Another thing that you can do to spice up your patio set is to add a few plants around your furniture. Bringing plants into the picture will add more color and make it a more inviting space. For an extra sparkle, you can hang up a string or two of lights; this serves two purposes&mdash;it provides extra light for when it&rsquo;s dark out, and it makes your yard look beautiful. These two styling tips can elevate the way your patio looks and feels.</p>

1754

1755

1756<h3>

1757What Will You Choose?</h3>

1758

1759

1760<p>

1761Outdoor seating can be for everyone! Because there is a variety of outdoor furniture available, it won&rsquo;t be hard to select outdoor furniture that you love. Select a patio set and style it from there and you won&rsquo;t be disappointed.</p>

1762

1763

1764<p>

1765If you&rsquo;re looking to add patio furniture to your backyard or you&rsquo;re wanting to renovate your outdoor space, our Vevano Home expert designers can help you! Feel free to reach out to them today for assistance.</p>

Furniture\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOutdoor furniture can transform your backyard, patio, or deck into a beautiful extension of your home. You can go simple and pair some lounge chairs with an outdoor fire pit, or you can go all out with a gazebo, a porch swing, and patio dining set. The choice is up to you!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe want to be your resource in understanding everything you need to know about outdoor furniture, from outlining what the\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-materials-outdoor-furniture/\"\u003ebest materials for outdoor furniture\u003c/a\u003e are to explaining\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-clean-outdoor-cushions/\"\u003ehow to clean outdoor cushions\u003c/a\u003e\u0026nbsp;and other furniture items. With the help of our \u003ca href=\"https://design.vevano.com/design-services/\"\u003eVevano Home\u0026rsquo;s expert designers\u003c/a\u003e, we share different types of outdoor furniture and how to style it and keep it clean.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eElevate Your Space with a New Patio Set\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA patio set consists of dining and side tables, chairs, cushions, umbrellas, and more. Because there are so many styles and design options to choose from, you can personalize your patio set to fit your unique style and make it as comfortable as you\u0026rsquo;d like.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen selecting a patio set, take into consideration the size of the available space that you have. If the space is large, make sure the outdoor furniture that you choose fills the space and has enough seating for the typical amounts of guests that you will have over. On the other hand, if your space is smaller, make sure that it doesn\u0026rsquo;t feel overcrowded with too much furniture or furniture that is too big.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are two types of patio sets: dining sets and lounge sets. Here\u0026rsquo;s a brief overview of each.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePatio Dining Sets\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDining sets are typically used for enjoying meals outside with family and friends. This piece of outdoor patio furniture should be comfortable enough for you and your guests to eat and converse for a couple of hours. That means that you\u0026rsquo;ll want to look for furniture that is made of metal or wood and is furnished with plush pillows and cushions on the seat and the back. These patio dining sets consist of five to eleven different pieces including dining tables, chairs, cushions, umbrellas, etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePatio Lounge Sets\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnother popular option for patio sets is a lounge set. Imagine a warm summer night, conversing with family, and laughing together. Your patio lounge set would be the perfect location for this. Having a sofa and comfortable chairs made of weatherproof outdoor furniture material would be ideal so that your furniture does not rust with rain or fade with time. These patio lounge sets can consist of a coffee table or a couple of side tables, chairs, a hammock, a sofa or chaise lounge, and an umbrella to provide share while enjoying your backyard.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026rsquo;re looking for something a little more simple and budget-friendly, you can take a look at bistro sets. These sets are composed of two chairs with a table in between. Bistro sets are a great option if you don\u0026rsquo;t need a ton of seating, but still want to enjoy those summer nights outside.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eCommon Patio Set Materials\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are several different types of materials that patio sets are made of. We have compiled a list of the top four best outdoor weatherproof materials.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWrought Iron\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWrought iron makes for durable furniture and provides sturdy chairs and tables. Because of this, cast iron furniture is more heavy, so if you\u0026rsquo;re wanting to move your furniture around a lot, remember that it may be more difficult to move. You will also want to make sure that your cast iron furniture has a weather resistant finish so that it does not rust when it gets wet.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTeak\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis material is a very popular option because teak is the hardest, strongest, and most durable of the hardwoods. Because of its ability to last long, many people choose teak for their outdoor furniture. Teak is also less maintenance than cast iron because it is already weather and pest resistant. The natural oils found in teak repel water, so you don\u0026rsquo;t have to worry about it being exposed to the rain.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSunbrella or Olefin\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSunbrella and Olefin are highly-durable outdoor fabric materials. Both materials are fade- and water-resistant and hold up well under a variety of weather conditions\u0026mdash;although we still recommend covering or stowing away outdoor furniture under extreme weather. Sunbrella tends to have better water-resistance, but Olefin is more durable and eco-friendly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConcrete\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eConcrete is a trending for outdoor furniture\u0026mdash;and it\u0026rsquo;s no surprise why. This highly durable, versatile material pairs well with most outdoor materials, including teak and wrought iron. Depending on how you style it, concrete can add a modern, sophisticated touch to your space or lend to a rustic ambience.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSynthetic Woven Resin\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWho doesn\u0026rsquo;t love the look of rattan woven in a stylish criss-cross wicker pattern? Unfortunately, natural rattan and other plant fibers require lots of maintenance and are prone to fading and water damage. However, synthetic resin and plastic are wonderfully durable alternatives to natural plant fibers and can mimic the same classic wicker look and weaves you want in outdoor furniture. Look for synthetic woven textures made of high-density polyethylene (HDPE) for maximum durability.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eHow to Keep Your Outdoor Furniture Clean\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo be able to enjoy your outdoor patio furniture for years to come, you will want to take care of it properly. Before purchasing any outdoor furniture, make sure that it is made of materials that are built to last and are rust resistant. You can then protect your furniture from harsh weather by using furniture covers. We recommend covering your outdoor furniture whenever you are not using it but especially when you are storing them away for the season.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you use pillows and cushions that have a protective case, you can throw the cases in the washer a couple of times a year so they look new again. If your cushions do not have a protective case or they are not machine washable, you can wash your furniture with the hose and dish soap to get some of those tough stains out of the fabric.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen cleaning your cushions, use a hard brush to scrub out those hard stains, and then let them air dry in the sun. You\u0026rsquo;ll want to make sure that you do this on a solid outdoor surface. For best results when cleaning your outdoor furniture cushions, use a pressure washer to get out tough stains.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe effort that you will need to put in to maintain your set looking nice will depend on the climate where you live. Be sure to research and choose materials that respond well to your location\u0026rsquo;s climate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eOutdoor Furniture Styling Tips\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBecause there are so many options of what you can do with outdoor furniture, the styling possibilities are endless! If desired, keep your patio set in a similar style as the rest of your house and rooms indoor. For example, if you have a modern kitchen, pair it with a modern outdoor furniture set. There are also contemporary, coastal, rustic, exotic, and so many more styles. Pick what you like the best and style it with some matching cushions and pillows and your patio set will \u0026lsquo;wow\u0026rsquo; your guests.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnother thing that you can do to spice up your patio set is to add a few plants around your furniture. Bringing plants into the picture will add more color and make it a more inviting space. You can go simple and pair some lounge chairs with an outdoor fire pit, or you can go all out with a gazebo, a porch swing, and patio dining set. The choice is up to you!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe want to be your resource in understanding everything you need to know about outdoor furniture, from outlining what the\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-materials-outdoor-furniture/\"\u003ebest materials for outdoor furniture\u003c/a\u003e are to explaining\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-clean-outdoor-cushions/\"\u003ehow to clean outdoor cushions\u003c/a\u003e\u0026nbsp;and other furniture items. With the help of our \u003ca href=\"https://design.vevano.com/design-services/\"\u003eVevano Home\u0026rsquo;s expert designers\u003c/a\u003e, we share different types of outdoor furniture and how to style it and keep it clean.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eElevate Your Space with a New Patio Set\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA patio set consists of dining and side tables, chairs, cushions, umbrellas, and more. Because there are so many styles and design options to choose from, you can personalize your patio set to fit your unique style and make it as comfortable as you\u0026rsquo;d like.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen selecting a patio set, take into consideration the size of the available space that you have. If the space is large, make sure the outdoor furniture that you choose fills the space and has enough seating for the typical amounts of guests that you will have over. On the other hand, if your space is smaller, make sure that it doesn\u0026rsquo;t feel overcrowded with too much furniture or furniture that is too big.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are two types of patio sets: dining sets and lounge sets. Here\u0026rsquo;s a brief overview of each.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePatio Dining Sets\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDining sets are typically used for enjoying meals outside with family and friends. This piece of outdoor patio furniture should be comfortable enough for you and your guests to eat and converse for a couple of hours. That means that you\u0026rsquo;ll want to look for furniture that is made of metal or wood and is furnished with plush pillows and cushions on the seat and the back. These patio dining sets consist of five to eleven different pieces including dining tables, chairs, cushions, umbrellas, etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePatio Lounge Sets\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnother popular option for patio sets is a lounge set. Imagine a warm summer night, conversing with family, and laughing together. Your patio lounge set would be the perfect location for this. Having a sofa and comfortable chairs made of weatherproof outdoor furniture material would be ideal so that your furniture does not rust with rain or fade with time. These patio lounge sets can consist of a coffee table or a couple of side tables, chairs, a hammock, a sofa or chaise lounge, and an umbrella to provide share while enjoying your backyard.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026rsquo;re looking for something a little more simple and budget-friendly, you can take a look at bistro sets. These sets are composed of two chairs with a table in between. Bistro sets are a great option if you don\u0026rsquo;t need a ton of seating, but still want to enjoy those summer nights outside.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eCommon Patio Set Materials\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are several different types of materials that patio sets are made of. We have compiled a list of the top four best outdoor weatherproof materials.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWrought Iron\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWrought iron makes for durable furniture and provides sturdy chairs and tables. Because of this, cast iron furniture is more heavy, so if you\u0026rsquo;re wanting to move your furniture around a lot, remember that it may be more difficult to move. You will also want to make sure that your cast iron furniture has a weather resistant finish so that it does not rust when it gets wet.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTeak\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis material is a very popular option because teak is the hardest, strongest, and most durable of the hardwoods. Because of its ability to last long, many people choose teak for their outdoor furniture. Teak is also less maintenance than cast iron because it is already weather and pest resistant. The natural oils found in teak repel water, so you don\u0026rsquo;t have to worry about it being exposed to the rain.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSunbrella or Olefin\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSunbrella and Olefin are highly-durable outdoor fabric materials. Both materials are fade- and water-resistant and hold up well under a variety of weather conditions\u0026mdash;although we still recommend covering or stowing away outdoor furniture under extreme weather. Sunbrella tends to have better water-resistance, but Olefin is more durable and eco-friendly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConcrete\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eConcrete is a trending for outdoor furniture\u0026mdash;and it\u0026rsquo;s no surprise why. This highly durable, versatile material pairs well with most outdoor materials, including teak and wrought iron. Depending on how you style it, concrete can add a modern, sophisticated touch to your space or lend to a rustic ambience.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSynthetic Woven Resin\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWho doesn\u0026rsquo;t love the look of rattan woven in a stylish criss-cross wicker pattern? Unfortunately, natural rattan and other plant fibers require lots of maintenance and are prone to fading and water damage. However, synthetic resin and plastic are wonderfully durable alternatives to natural plant fibers and can mimic the same classic wicker look and weaves you want in outdoor furniture. Look for synthetic woven textures made of high-density polyethylene (HDPE) for maximum durability.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eHow to Keep Your Outdoor Furniture Clean\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo be able to enjoy your outdoor patio furniture for years to come, you will want to take care of it properly. Before purchasing any outdoor furniture, make sure that it is made of materials that are built to last and are rust resistant. You can then protect your furniture from harsh weather by using furniture covers. We recommend covering your outdoor furniture whenever you are not using it but especially when you are storing them away for the season.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you use pillows and cushions that have a protective case, you can throw the cases in the washer a couple of times a year so they look new again. If your cushions do not have a protective case or they are not machine washable, you can wash your furniture with the hose and dish soap to get some of those tough stains out of the fabric.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen cleaning your cushions, use a hard brush to scrub out those hard stains, and then let them air dry in the sun. You\u0026rsquo;ll want to make sure that you do this on a solid outdoor surface. For best results when cleaning your outdoor furniture cushions, use a pressure washer to get out tough stains.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe effort that you will need to put in to maintain your set looking nice will depend on the climate where you live. Be sure to research and choose materials that respond well to your location\u0026rsquo;s climate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eOutdoor Furniture Styling Tips\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBecause there are so many options of what you can do with outdoor furniture, the styling possibilities are endless! If desired, keep your patio set in a similar style as the rest of your house and rooms indoor. For example, if you have a modern kitchen, pair it with a modern outdoor furniture set. There are also contemporary, coastal, rustic, exotic, and so many more styles. Pick what you like the best and style it with some matching cushions and pillows and your patio set will \u0026lsquo;wow\u0026rsquo; your guests.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnother thing that you can do to spice up your patio set is to add a few plants around your furniture. Bringing plants into the picture will add more color and make it a more inviting space. For an extra sparkle, you can hang up a string or two of lights; this serves two purposes\u0026mdash;it provides extra light for when it\u0026rsquo;s dark out, and it makes your yard look beautiful. These two styling tips can elevate the way your patio looks and feels.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat Will You Choose?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOutdoor seating can be for everyone!
